# check-back-intelligence

Read [`check-back-intelligence/CLAUDE.md`](~/Documents/GitHub/check-back-intelligence/CLAUDE.md) first.

## Commands

```bash
cd ~/Documents/GitHub/check-back-intelligence
pip install -r requirements.txt
python -m src.cli populate --sources <folder> --out output/<name>.xlsx
python -m src.cli validate -i output/<name>.xlsx --out staging/validation.json
open ~/Documents/GitHub/check-back-intelligence/dashboard/index.html
```

## Conventions

- Dashboard accepts **populated xlsx only** — not raw PDFs/images.
- Deliverables to `/Users/konyebin/CLAUDE/` when user asks for exports.
- **Never commit** customer PDFs, screenshots with PII, or `.env` tokens.
- Template: `samples/check_back_template.xlsx`.

## Verification

After populate: run `validate` and confirm row counts in CLI output before saying done.
